  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td style="vertical-align: top;">
      <h1 style="text-align: center;"><big>Cannon</big><br>
      </h1>
Cannon is a modern capturing game in the same general group as
Chess.&nbsp; Each player has a phalanx of soldiers, and attempts to
capture the opponent's town piece.&nbsp; Soldiers generally only move
forward, but can retreat if threatened.&nbsp; The defining feature of
the game is that a line of three soldiers forms a cannon which can
capture at a distance.&nbsp; Those are the headlines, read the complete
      <a
 href="http://www.pyromythgames.com/products/cannon/Cannonrules.htm">rules



      </a>here.<br>
      <br>
Cannon is a very tactical game.<br>
      <br>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">Robots:</span>&nbsp; Barely
adequate.<br>
      </td>
      <td style="vertical-align: top;"><img
 style="width: 540px; height: 544px;" alt="cannon image"
 src="../images/cannon-small.jpg"><br>
      </td>
    </tr>
